    "body": "This is the result of applying https://github.com/KMiri-rs/miri/commit/1b6f26e0a0b24e88f228d92ab363bc21c061735e . When the address has multiple AllocIds, kmiri can't interpret the address correctly.\n\n```rust\nerror: Undefined Behavior: constructing invalid value of type core::fmt::Arguments<'_>: at .template, encountered 0, but expected something greater or equal to 1\n   --> /home/zjp/.rustup/toolchains/nightly-2026-04-03-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/lib/rustlib/src/rust/library/core/src/fmt/mod.rs:236:33\n    |\n236 |                     write(self, args)\n    |                                 ^^^^ Undefined Behavior occurred here\n    |\n    = help: this indicates a bug in the program: it performed an invalid operation, and caused Undefined Behavior\n    = help: see https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/reference/behavior-considered-undefined.html for further information\n    = note: stack backtrace:\n            0: <&mut ostd::arch::MiriStdout as core::fmt::Write::write_fmt::SpecWriteFmt>::spec_write_fmt\n                at /home/zjp/.rustup/toolchains/nightly-2026-04-03-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/lib/rustlib/src/rust/library/core/src/fmt/mod.rs:236:33: 236:37\n            1: <ostd::arch::MiriStdout as core::fmt::Write>::write_fmt\n                at /home/zjp/.rustup/toolchains/nightly-2026-04-03-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/lib/rustlib/src/rust/library/core/src/fmt/mod.rs:241:9: 241:34\n            2: ostd::arch::_miri_print\n                at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/arch/miri/mod.rs:141:5: 141:31\n            3: miri_start\n                at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/lib.rs:39:9: 39:69\n```",
